OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1780323077
OL,3,CWill the taps run dry over the summer?
OL,5,FOn one day this week, 670 million
OL,6,Flitres of drinking water were used,
OL,7,Fwhich South East water said is almost
OL,8,F100 million litres more than the
OL,9,Faverage for this time of the year.
OL,11,FSo could we see similar issues here in
OL,12,Fthe Midlands?
OL,14,FSevern Trent's reservoirs are
OL,15,Fcurrently at 90% capacity - that's
OL,16,Fcompared to 95.7% two months ago.
OL,18,FThey said, "We work hard to secure our
OL,19,Fwater supply and that's why there's
OL,20,Fbeen no summertime restrictions in our
OL,21,Fregion for 30 years.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1780323077
OL,3,CWill the taps run dry over the summer?
OL,5,F"Some areas in our region are
OL,6,Fnaturally more water stressed than
OL,7,Fothers, but with an ever-changing
OL,8,Fclimate, we have a number of options
OL,9,Fto draw on.
OL,11,F"This includes a healthy mix of
OL,12,Freservoirs, rivers, boreholes and
OL,13,Fsprings - which helps make sure water
OL,14,Fcan continue to get to where it's
OL,15,Fneeded and our reservoir levels remain
OL,16,Fhealthy at 90%."
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
